<p>So as the title says, I'm trying to have my Navbar using Twitter Bootstrap to have different colors when hovering over particular buttons. Here is my index.html code snippet:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;nav class="navbar navbar-inverse navbar-fixed-top"&gt;   &lt;div class="container-fluid"&gt;     &lt;div class="navbar-header"&gt;       &lt;button type="button" class="navbar-toggle" data-toggle="collapse"       data-target="#myNavbar"&gt;         &lt;span class="icon-bar"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;         &lt;span class="icon-bar"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;         &lt;span class="icon-bar"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;       &lt;/button&gt;       &lt;a class="navbar-brand" href="#"&gt;Frank does...&lt;/a&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="myNavbar"&gt;       &lt;ul class="nav navbar-nav"&gt;         &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Home&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;         &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Page 1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;         &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Page 2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;         &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Page 3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;       &lt;/ul&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/nav&gt; </code></pre>  <p>The goal is to have the different buttons on the navbar (page 1, page 2, etc.,) be different colors. However, I don't know how to do that. I tried placing <code>&lt;Div&gt;</code> on the <code>li</code> elements such as:</p>  <p><code>&lt;div class="home"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Home&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</code></p>  <p>but that somehow messes up the structure of the navbar, messing up the navbar and making the home button go above the navbar.</p>  <p>How can I make it so that each <code>li</code> element can have its own <code>hover</code> color?</p>  <p>Also, here is my CSS code that changes the hover color to red, but only red. </p>  <pre><code>.navbar-inverse .navbar-collapse li a:hover, .navbar-inverse .navbar-collapse li a:focus{     background-color:red; } </code></pre>